text: Teodora Špirić (born 12 April 2000), known professionally as Teya and formerly Thea Devy, is an Austrian-Serbian singer and songwriter. In 2023, it was announced that she would represent Austria in Eurovision 2023, alongside Austrian singer Salena, with the song "Who the Hell is Edgar?". They finished in 15th place out of the 26 finalists. The two have also made other songs called "Bye Bye Bye" and "Ho Ho Ho" before they began solo careers at the end of 2023. == References == Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:People from Vienna Category:Austrian singers Category:Eurovision Song Contest entrants
